<br>
   I found out who was leading the raid and sent him a tell asking if I can go, he agreed so I was on my way to Permafrost. While in North Karana, I met a warrior, Azeroth, who had also been running to Permafrost for the vox raid so we ran there together.<br>
<br>
   I had never been to Permafrost before, seeing as how it was way off in the distance. I had never had a need or urge to go there, so this would be my first trip there. <br>
<br>
   After being lost in Everfrost for about 15 minutes with Azeroth we finally stumped across the Permafrost zone by accident and met up with everyone else.<br>
<br>
   We headed in, buffed up, grouped everyone, and had the occasion fun stuff. Some people would mess around and tell jokes while others would intentionally train us with goblins to liven things up.<br>
   <br>
   Finally we began moving in. Seemed like forever until we finally got to the buffing hall. A few people had messed up the pulls, others had pets which aggroed vox, etc. Typical stuff for us back then, we didn't know any better.<br>
<br>
   After about an hour of buffing up and moving to the chat room it was finally time to move into Vox's lair. We all logged in and got ready to charge. I had borrowed tons of resist gear from a friend, so wasn't really concerned with being feared or AE'd. I was a 52 druid with about 100 unbuffed MR and CR, which I then had Circle of SUmmer and bard song.<br>
<br>
   Charging Vox had to be the most incredible thing I've seen in this game. It was the first major mob I had ever attempted. I ran in and immediately noticed about 4 corpses and kind of realized we wouldn't take her. As i stood back healing for the first few seconds I saw more and more people being feared right by me and more and more people dying all over the lair. Then i heard my command. Nuke! I ran in landed 2 Starfire's off on Vox before she sent me back to the orb in TT. Lucky for us there had been no necro's on the raid, which made the CR incredibly slow.<br>
<br>
   I ran back to Perma naked, and tried to meet up with everyone at the gates leading to the forst giants. Little had I realized there was no one in the zone except me, and I ran just run into my inevitable death. I died again to the hands of the goblins seeing as how i didn't have gate up and didn't know my way around the zone well enough to escape. I lost that corpse and didn't receive a rez. I became frustrated and decided to log.<br>
<br>
   The next day I received help from a friendly necro which i was guilded with, and got a rez from a cleric that had camped in Permafrost.<br>
<br>
   Although, it wasn't a triumphant experience, it was a great one. Now i read these posts and everyone takes down Vox and Naggy. /shrug For real fun you gotta lose sometimes, don't make it look too easy! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
